-<p><a name="st_117"></a>
-<a name="06100910000314"></a><b><a name="61009-0008.htm_spnew0"></a><a name="06100910001463"></a>Lord Bassam of Brighton:</b> My Lords, I listened carefully to what the noble Baroness said on this matter, not for the first time, and I conclude that, while this is an interesting debate, it is a debate about means and the ends are shared. We all want to see standards raised and plans actively pursued and fulfilled. I do not think it is essential to have this provision in the Bill. In fact, by putting it there, we may be constraining ourselves and removing an important and necessary element of flexibility to reflect and change priorities over time. I heard what the noble Baroness said on this issue, but I am not persuaded and I have to insist on the Government&#146;s amendment.</p>
