+<a name="61009-0015.htm_para34"></a>
+<p><a name="stpa_362"></a><a name="06100910000604"></a>The order allows the Government to raise the legal age at which tobacco can be bought to any age, as the Minister highlighted. The Health Bill for the United Kingdom states that the age should not be raised above 18 years. Why is that not included in this Bill? In principle, we support the order, but I am extremely unhappy at how it has been put together.</p>
